Text.Value: Just me and you. I like that. Harmless little secret.

EditorData.NodeContext: Realises what this means - he can pick you off

Text.Value: I've come from Darkhold. I'm here to join the Zhentarim inside.
Found? Found? You STOLE!

EditorData.NodeContext: Angry/Accusing

Text.Value: Bloody Darkhold Zhents. Getting paid to lurk in our Guildhall. Never work for it.
Big words from such a puny mouth. Let's see how strong you really are.
Thank you for the list - now I know which parts of you to break first.
*Though you can't shake the feeling you've seen it before, the emblem's purpose is beyond your recall.*
Follow me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Urgent

Text.Value: Eyes to yourself, elf.
Read the muscle-bound half-orc's mind.
Oh, but surely we're safe with one of Nine-Fingers' big strapping boys to protect us.
Thieving Zhent scum.

EditorData.NodeContext: Furious

Text.Value: Look closer at the ring. Try to recall the symbol's meaning.
Come. I'll take you to the Guildhall. Nine-Fingers is inside.
That's why Nine-Fingers asked me to guard the entrance to the Guildhall.

EditorData.NodeContext: Showing off

Text.Value: Surely one little peep won't hurt? It can be our little secret.
Farlin said to let you in this time. Very insistent.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a sigh - he's a bit reluctant, but likes Farlin so will do what she asked

Text.Value: Did I whisper? I said GET LOST.

EditorData.NodeContext: Threatening, spelling out "Get Lost" like he's speaking to an idiot

Text.Value: I said you could come in. Didn't say you could leave.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a smile - about to have some fun

Text.Value: You're here to see Nine-Fingers? She didn't tell me.
Come in. Take a look around.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: with a smile - he's plotting something, not particularly subtle

Text.Value: I'm here to see Nine-Fingers. Get in my way, and you'll lose more than your ring finger.
Jaheira...? The same Jaheira who burned down Fugal's tea-shop? I saw that fire. Very big. Strange smell.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little fearful but trying not to show it. He's just unwittingly bad-mouthed someone with quite a reputation. At the end, recollecting something interesting.

Text.Value: Guarding the secret entrance? Not good enough for them. But good enough for poor old Tusgront.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Moaning/Lamenting the boring job he's been given

Text.Value: All better now though.

EditorData.NodeContext: Pleased, apparently unaware that he is currently slow and stupid

Text.Value: You think I'm stupid? Well, I think you're dead.

EditorData.NodeContext: COMBAT

Text.Value: Lot of people lose things in this alley. Like their LIVES.

EditorData.NodeContext: Threatening, thinks he's being very witty

Text.Value: Leave.

EditorData.NodeContext: Remembering a past vigilante effort of Jaheira's (FOO-gill)

Text.Value: I found this strange ring. Do you know anything about it?
Secrets are good. Violence is better.

EditorData.NodeContext: Smirking - he's about to kill you

Text.Value: Go on, then. If the guildmaster doesn't want you in her hall, she'll tell you so herself.

EditorData.NodeContext: Letting you past

Text.Value: Harm can be anywhere you like - nose, kneecaps, fingernails...

EditorData.NodeContext: Threatening, with a smile

Text.Value: *On the half-orc's finger, you notice an unusual ring: heavy, and with a strange symbol carved on its surface.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shot on orc's hand, ring visible

Text.Value: Shouldn't go wandering in dark alleys. Very dangerous hobby. Gets people killed.

EditorData.NodeContext: Scolding

Text.Value: Not if I tear yours out first.

EditorData.NodeContext: Threatening

Text.Value: The Zhents? Interesting...

EditorData.NodeContext: Dawning horror

Text.Value: Peace, peace. Fearsome individuals always welcome in Tusgront's alley.

EditorData.NodeContext: Calming you, with a smile - he doesn't think you're fearsome at all

Text.Value: Peace, peace. Your belly burns too hot. It's just a simple alleyway.

EditorData.NodeContext: with a smile - not scared in the slightest

Text.Value: You again.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not giving much away

Text.Value: Take me to Nine-Fingers, or I swear on Gruumsh's eye, I'll tear you limb from limb.
Do not worry. Guild's friends are Tusgront's friends.
Leave.
Stop! What are you doing? Are you trying to sneak past Tusgront?

EditorData.NodeContext: Accusing, sense of threat building
EditorData.logicalname: HasNotMet - Exits Guildhall, hasn't been seen

Text.Value: When I kill you, you won't have time to scream.

EditorData.NodeContext: Threatening

Text.Value: Look closer at the ring. Try to recall the symbol's meaning.
You have a death wish? I said CLEAR OFF.

EditorData.NodeContext: Threatening, spelling out "Clear off" like he's speaking to an idiot

Text.Value: Another one come to take our coin and clog our halls.

EditorData.NodeContext: muttering, exasperated

Text.Value: I just want a quick look around. Where's the harm?
And I don't hurt my friends. Unless they deserve it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Breaking the tension - he was toying with you. Still a slight hint of threat at the end

Text.Value: I am handsome. Also very strong. And smart. And dis-creet.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Indicates his discretion on "dis-creet" - taps side of nose or similar
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: blushing, posturing. Doesn't really know what "discrete" means
EditorData.NodeContext: blushing, posturing. Doesn't really know what "discrete" means

Text.Value: Something valuable? Then you must get it back.

EditorData.NodeContext: pretending to be helpful

Text.Value: Leave.
*You recall seeing this symbol on crates marked for Nine-Fingers Keene, leader of the Guild. The thug works for her.*
Trying to read my thoughts? Read THIS.
Fine - I'll show you in. Nine-Fingers will give you orders.

EditorData.NodeContext: with a sigh, has no choice

Text.Value: Go on down. Tusgront is keeping watch.

EditorData.NodeContext: Determined

Text.Value: Let me through, or I swear on Gruumsh's eye I'll tear your limbs from their sockets.
Always 'Don't let anyone through, Tusgront.' Never 'Here's a list of special guests.' Confusing.
Nasty little tea man. Sold me some of his rotten leaves once. Made me feel slow, and stupid.

EditorData.NodeContext: Vague approval - grateful that Jaheira shut down a narcotic tea shop, annoyed at the memory of having been tricked

Text.Value: I've come to warn Nine-Fingers. The Zhentarim are planning to kill her.
Funny little gnome, she is - always laughing at me. Even when I don't joke.

EditorData.NodeContext: Oblivious to the fact Farlin is mocking him, thinks she's just a good-natured little gnome

Text.Value: The fire was his own fault. Bad enough he was adding silkroot to his brews - but he stored it poorly, too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not fully defensive, but correcting the record - she only went to shut down a drugs operation, the fire was entirely incidental

Text.Value: Hate to cut short conversation with such a handsome fellow, but I have urgent business with Nine-Fingers...
Are you lost? Or just stupid? Go. Away.

EditorData.NodeContext: Toying with you, threatening

Text.Value: Of - of course! She didn't tell me you were coming.

EditorData.NodeContext: bit flustered, trying to act like he knows who the player is (he doesn't)

Text.Value: Sneaking into MY ALLEY?! Nobody sneaks into MY ALLEY!

EditorData.NodeContext: shouted, getting the attention of the other guards a few metres away

Text.Value: Are those your final words? Usually people scream for their mothers.
Wait. Where's my ring? Did you take my ring?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Checks hand/notices ring is missing (doesn't need to be shown in close-up)

Text.Value: Handsome - not stupid. Stupid is trying to trick me...
No need for violence, friend. Just doing my job.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Throws up hands - I'm not a threat
EditorData.NodeContext: Pacifying

Text.Value: People think they can sneak past me: Fists, adventurers, journalists... Got to be on my guard.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confiding his woes

Text.Value: You won't be telling her anything. 'Cause you'll be dead.
Careful - that's High Harper Jaheira you're speaking to.
Boss doesn't like outsiders sniffing around.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a smile - about to have some fun

Text.Value: Shall I tell Nine-Fingers you refused to let me pass? She'll be very unhappy.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - Holding pattern for Tusgront

Text.Value: Oi. Stop staring. Start walking. Last chance.
You don't recognise me? I'm Nine-Fingers' right hand. She needs me immediately.
It is true. Boo has slain many who have greeted him so impolitely.
I came by earlier and lost something. I just want to retrieve it.
Scuttle away, lizard. Before I cut off your tail.
Go back to your mine, dglinkarz. Before I bury you myself.
Walk away, nothrakash. While you still have legs.
Scurry away, gubuk. Before I crush you.

EditorData.NodeContext:
Menacing. 
"dglinkarz" = glin-KARZ (roughly equal emphasis on both syllables, with a strong k to start the second syllable. "Karz"  like "cars", but elongating the a and z).  
"Gubuk" - GU-buk (Both "u"s as in "push"/"look"/"book"). 
"Nothrakash" - noth-RAK-ash (Harsh, slightly rolled "r".)

Text.Value: That's her sigil on your ring, is it not?
I'm Nine Fingers new muscle. Let me pass, or I'l show you why I was hired.
Wait. You're Farlin's friend... She said to let you in.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slowly catching on, then becoming friendly

Text.Value: What's with that strange wall over there? Is that what you're guarding?
Attack.
Come. I'll let you in. My pleasure.

Synopsis: Dialogue with the main guard in the Undercellar Entrance, where the player can try to detect what are they guarding and convince them to allow access.
